If you are interested in more, it's the average number of runs (earned) that a pitcher statistically gives up in nine innings.

Earned runs are runs that score without an error.  For example, if there is a runner on third base and the right fielder misses a relatively easy catch and the runner scores, that is not an earned run, and is not counted in his stats.

