@Jane Wheelaghan

Hi Jane, if a pitcher "gives up" or allows a run, it means that he has allowed a player to score, which can happen in a number of ways. For example, the batter might get a home run, or a hit or bunt with someone on third base who is then able to score.

The formula uses nine innings to find the average because that is the usual length of a game, but most pitchers do not pitch a full game. Perhaps most confusing, a pitcher can be "responsible" for runners still on base after he leaves the game, and can earn runs if those players score.

